                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has the opinion of the court in two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 4.976,
                        "stop": 206.352,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.976,
                                "stop": 12.884,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The first case I have is McFadden v. United States No. 14-378."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.884,
                                "stop": 19.724,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.724,
                                "stop": 42.438,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Petitioner Stephen McFadden came to the attention of law enforcement agents because he was supplying a Charlottesville video store with certain recreational drugs known as bath salts; a sentence which I completely do not understand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.438,
                                "stop": 56.796,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Those drugs have chemical structures substantially similar to controlled substances and are capable of producing effects substantially similar to those produced by controlled substances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.796,
                                "stop": 65.026,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under Federal Law these features qualify the drugs as \u201ccontrolled substances analogues.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.026,
                                "stop": 72.278,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "McFadden eventually was convicted of eight counts of distribution of such analogues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.278,
                                "stop": 92.414,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "On appeal he argued that the District Court should have instructed the jury that it could not convict him unless he knew the chemical structure and pharmacological effects of the substances that brought them within the definition of controlled substance analogues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.414,
                                "stop": 102.544,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Fourth Circuit rejected the argument, concluding that McFadden needed only to intend the substances to be consumed by humans."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.544,
                                "stop": 106.173,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It therefore affirmed his convictions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.173,
                                "stop": 113.97,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the court today we reverse the judgment of the Fourth Circuit and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.97,
                                "stop": 128.747,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under the Controlled Substances Act it is \u201cunlawful for any person knowingly or intentionally\u201d to possess with the intent to distribute a controlled substance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.747,
                                "stop": 148.245,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That intent requirement is met either if defendant knows he possesses a substance that is controlled even if he does not know its identity, or if he knows the identity of the substance he possessed; even if he does not know that it is controlled."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.245,
                                "stop": 162.574,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Because the Federal Analogue Act instructs courts to treat controlled substance analogues as controlled substances the same mental state applies to prosecutions involving analogues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.574,
                                "stop": 179.526,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A defendant has the requisite intent if he knows he possesses some substance regulated under the Controlled Substances Act or the Analogue Act or if he knows the features of the substance that make it an analogue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.526,
                                "stop": 185.851,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The jury instruction in this case did not adequately convey this required mental state."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.851,
                                "stop": 199.4,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others set forth in our opinion we reverse the judgment of the Fourth Circuit and remand for that court to consider whether the jury instruction error here was harmless or not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.4,
                                "stop": 206.352,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
